HOW TO BUILD IT

Install libdb_cxx and libfltk development files

Download the code

$ tar xzf coyotetm-<latest-version>.tgz
$ cd coyotetm
$ ./configure
$ make
$ sudo make install

HOW TO EXECUTE IT

$ /usr/local/bin/coyotetm

It will create ~/coyotetm directory for database files

You have three arguments:
--dump
   it will dump the data in a text format to you stdout
--reindex
   if for whatever reason the application crash, it might
   damage your index, so just reindexit
--version
   application version

FLATPAK

You can download the flatpak version from https://flathub.org/en/apps/io.github.igaldino.CoyoteTM

In order to use the home directory to store tasks, override flatpak's default:

$ flatpak override --user --filesystem=/home/you/coyotetm io.github.igaldino.CoyoteTM
